<br>
My question has to do with the Color series.  They are point blank area stuns in a tight radius around you.  Will they break a mezzed mob that is in the radius?<br>
<br>
I was going to use it to buy time to be able to get off a mez. I hear that Whirl won't work on the higher level mobs and Dyn's take too much mana.<br>
<br>
Will the lower level color stun work on higher level mobs (40s)?<br>
<br>
Should I use root for this kind of crowd control?  If so, I'm sure it would be the low level root, not Instill.<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance,<br>
<br>
Jababar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=charmroxors>Charmroxors</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#330000>(2/17/03 2:27:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Point Blank Stuns</span><hr size=1> point blank stuns are somethin i usually never use...your color series should be good enough to keep your cc in check... the level 30something color stun (entrancing lights..?), keeps them stunned long enough to remez usually. <br>
