<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=412864">Stylina, Coercer of the Rathe</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(2/25/03 5:20:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Point Blank Stuns</span><hr size=1> First to answer some questions:<br>
<br>
1) PBAE stuns and mezzes do not break mez.  Nothing that does not do damage (reduce hp) breaks mez.<br>
<br>
2) PBAE stuns (color series) work on mobs up to lvl 55, basically anything you can use regular mezzes on (mesmerize, enthrall, entrance, dazzle).<br>
<br>
3) Word of Morell is the PBAE stun equivalent of the color series at high lvls.  It's actually a mez though.<br>
<br>
4) Any mez will overwrite any other mez, so you can mez over entrancing lights or a color series spell.<br>
<br>
My style is somewhat different from Stylina's.  When I am dealing with mobs 55 and under, i mem dazzle (or maybe gok now for no recast) as well as color flux and color slant.  Color flux is my first choice for stunning.  The trick here is that whenever you use it, you target the mob you want to mez first.  Then you hit color flux, then back up immediately while the spell gem turns over.  As soon as dazzle or gok comes up, you cast mez.  Unless the mob summons and is damaged, this distance will give you the time to mez.  I prefer color flux to other stuns because it is a 1.0s cast time and very very easy to channel.<br>
<br>
I use the same approach with word of morell and CoD.  If i land word of morell, i just back up while CoD comes up and then cast immediately, I can always get it off.<br>
<br>
